Class GraphicList

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData

        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.GraphicList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GraphicList
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {GR?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    List of Graphics loaded in the printer.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GraphicList

        public GraphicList(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

    • Method Detail

      • getGraphics_IsPresent

        public boolean getGraphics_IsPresent()
        Indicates if getGraphics() parameter is present.

        This function is useful to determine if the given parameter is supported on the current printer. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned by the parameter getGraphics() may not be valid.

        Returns:
        If the parameter is present and valid true, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        getGraphics()

      • getGraphics

        public java.util.List<GraphicData> getGraphics()
        List of Graphics loaded in the printer.

        The return value for this parameter is only valid if getGraphics_IsPresent() returns true. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned may not be valid.

        Returns:
        The current value for the parameter.
        See Also:
        getGraphics_IsPresent()
